Subject: Notostira elongata 
To: Norman
Content:
Notostira elongata is a species of bugs from a Miridae family, that can be found throughout the United Kingdom. Adult size is 7.58.0 millimetres (0.300.31 in). The species have longitudinal furrow between the eyes, and are yellowish-green. Their prothorax is unpunctured and smooth, with dense dark hairs.[1] The species live two generations. The females change colour in fall, by becoming pinker, and larger. Both male and female species mate during winter, following by an egg development in spring. 
